service.name: Better Access Initiative (Mental Health Care)
service.description: The Better Access Initiative (Mental Health Care) is the government's commitment to provide better access to mental health care for patients with mental disorders includes Medicare Benefits Schedule items for consultant psychiatrists, general practitioners (GPs), psychologists, clinical psychologists, occupational therapists, social workers. Chronic Disease Management items continue to be available for patients with chronic medical conditions.
